n of vaping-related chemicals in the air were below occupational exposure limits or were not detectable at all.</span></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-131_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-132_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0743/6343/t/49/assets/recycling--disposing-of-vapor-products-2-1635891515011_360x.jpg?v=1635891516" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0743/6343/t/49/assets/recycling--disposing-of-vapor-products-2-1635891515011.jpg?v=1635891516 1536w" width="360" height="337" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-cZMNgc fhouYJ pf-133_"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:8;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ctqQKy imxmpH pf-134_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bTfYFJ iRKxGS pf-135_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-137_">Proper Disposal of Vaporizers &amp; E-Cigs</span></h3><p class="sc-uojGG kNKBxk pf-138_ dropcap--none" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Dropcap" class="sc-bilyIR jnhdaL pf-139_">We</span><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cbTzjv cciAhs pf-140_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">at White Horse Vapor take the environment and our product impact very seriously.</span> Here is some helpful information in regard to proper disposal of all E-Cigarette products.<br><br>E-Cigarette and E-Liquid waste should not be thrown in the garbage, or E-Liquid dumped into the sink/toilet. The main factor in proper disposal of e-cig equipment/products is if the item has a removable battery or not. For disposable vape pens, the batteries are enclosed so there is no need to attempt to remove them. For any pre-filled cartridges or pods that still contain any e-liquid, they should not be rinsed out as that could turn the water into potential hazardous waste.<br><br>Any vape pens, e-cigarettes, batteries, and cartridges should be taken to your Household Hazardous Waste (HHW) Facility. The closest site to our Retail North Providence Location is the Rhode Island Resource Recovery Corporation located in Johnston, Rhode Island. You are able to schedule a free appointment from their website at <a href="https://www.rirrc.org/recycling-composting-disposal/hazardous-waste/household-hazardous-waste" target="_blank">Household Hazardous Waste | (RIRRC.org</a>) or over the phone at 401-942-1430 EXT 241.<br>For nationwide disposal, you can reference your closest HHW at <a href="https://search.earth911.com/" target="_blank">Recycling Center Search - Earth911.com</a></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-element-placeholder="true" data-parallax="false" class="sc-fHeRUh ixLxDV pf-141_    pf-bg-lazy" data-pf-type="Section"><span data-pf-placeholder="true">Section</span></div></div></div></div><script>window.__pagefly_setting__={"baseURL":"https://apps.pagefly.io","analyticsURL":"https://analytics.pagefly.io","isBackend":false,"cdnURL":"https://cdn.pagefly.io","pageflyVersion":"3.15.1","shopDomain":"white-horse-vapor.myshopify.com","elementData":{},"pageTitle":"Facts","pageType":"blog","pageId":"c012b871-88f3-4f8d-9c4a-bf86d3c4acc3","lazyLoad":true,"forceByPassGoogleLightHouse":false,"imageLazyLoad":true,"nativeImageLazyLoad":true,"useThemeJQ":false,"selectedFonts":{"Lato":{"400":0,"700":0}},"trackingIDs":[],"shopifyProxyPath":"/a/pf_preview"};window.__pagefly_setting__.moneyFormat={{shop.money_format|json}};</script><script src="https://cdn.pagefly.io/pagefly/3.15.1/core/helper.js" async></script> </article>
